text.paragraph:
The plasma concentration of cyclobenzaprine is increased in the elderly (see CLINICAL 
                           PHARMACOLOGY, Pharmacokinetics, Elderly
                           ). The elderly may also be more at risk for CNS adverse events such as hallucinations and confusion, cardiac events resulting in falls or other sequelae, drug-drug and drug-disease interactions. For these reasons, in the elderly, cyclobenzaprine should be used only if clearly needed. In such patients cyclobenzaprine hydrochloride tablets should be initiated with a 5 mg dose and titrated slowly upward.
